3. ADDITIONAL USE GRANT

You may use the Licensed Work for any purpose, including commercial use,
subject to the following provisions.


3.1 PERMITTED WITHOUT PRIOR APPROVAL

The following uses are permitted without contacting the Licensor:

  (a) Developing and selling plugins for the Exiv platform
  (b) Building commercial applications using Exiv APIs
  (c) Internal use within your organization, regardless of size
  (d) Offering consulting, support, training, or integration services
  (e) Embedding Exiv in products for small-scale commercial distribution
  (f) Educational, academic, and research purposes
  (g) Personal projects and experimentation


3.2 REQUIRES PRIOR WRITTEN APPROVAL

"Large-Scale Commercial Deployment" requires contacting the Licensor for
approval before proceeding. Large-Scale Commercial Deployment means any of
the following:

  (a) Annual revenue from Exiv-based products or services exceeding
      $100,000 USD
  (b) Serving more than 1,000 active end users or customers
  (c) Deployment by organizations with more than 50 employees
  (d) Offering Exiv as a managed service, hosted service, or SaaS platform

To request approval for Large-Scale Commercial Deployment, contact:

  Email:  exiv.project@proton.me
  Method: Submit a request describing your intended use case, scale,
          and commercial model

Approval requests will be reviewed promptly and in good faith. The Licensor
may grant approval unconditionally, or may propose additional licensing terms
such as revenue-sharing agreements, partnership arrangements, or other
mutually beneficial terms.


3.3 PROHIBITED USES

The following uses are prohibited regardless of scale:

  (a) Creating a forked platform that directly competes with the official
      Exiv ecosystem as an AI agent orchestration platform
  (b) Rebranding Exiv as your own product without substantial differentiation
  (c) Removing or obscuring copyright notices and license attributions

